---
import EnServicePage from '../../../components/EnServicePage.astro';
---

<EnServicePage
  title="HubSpot Implementation & Operations Support"
  description="Set up, improve, and operate HubSpot as part of your revenue system — not as a standalone tool setup project."
  heroTagline="Set up, improve, and operate HubSpot as part of your revenue system."
  heroBrief="We support HubSpot implementation, migration, workflow design, reporting, and operational improvement for teams that need more than basic setup."
  secondaryCta="View CRM / RevOps Implementation"
  secondaryCtaHref="/en/services/crm-revops-implementation/"
  problemItems={[
    "HubSpot is live but underused — most activity still happens in spreadsheets, email, or manual updates",
    "Lead routing is inconsistent, handoffs are missed, and follow-up depends on individual memory",
    "Reports are available but not connected to how the team makes decisions",
    "The portal was set up for general use but not configured for Japan-facing operations specifically",
  ]}
  problemClose="HubSpot setup and HubSpot adoption are different problems. Setup happens once. Adoption requires configuration that fits how the team actually works — and in Japan, that means accounting for specific sales cycles, communication norms, and reporting expectations."
  bestFitHeading="Who this is for"
  bestFitItems={[
    "Teams implementing HubSpot for the first time and needing it built to match their revenue model",
    "Organizations migrating to HubSpot from another CRM and needing clean data and process migration",
    "Teams with an existing HubSpot portal that has accumulated configuration debt and needs restructuring",
    "Japan-market teams needing HubSpot configured for Japan's sales cycle and communication norms",
    "Companies needing ongoing HubSpot operations support after initial implementation",
  ]}
  coversHeading="What we support"
  covers={[
    { body: "HubSpot portal setup and cleanup — new setup or reorganization of existing portal structure" },
    { body: "Marketing Hub and Sales Hub configuration — properties, pipelines, sequences, and team permissions" },
    { body: "Lifecycle stages and lead status design — definitions aligned to your revenue model and handoff rules" },
    { body: "Forms, lists, workflows, and automation — lead capture, routing, nurturing, and task logic" },
    { body: "Pipeline and deal stage configuration — stages that reflect how Japan-facing deals actually progress" },
    { body: "Reporting and dashboards — custom reports for marketing, sales, and leadership views" },
    { body: "Data migration and property design — clean import, deduplication, and field mapping" },
    { body: "Operational documentation and enablement — how-to guides and team-specific usage rules" },
  ]}
  calloutHeading="Not just setup"
  calloutBody="We do not treat HubSpot as a standalone tool setup project. We connect configuration decisions to funnel design, team ownership, reporting needs, and daily operating rules. HubSpot should reflect how your revenue process works — not what the default onboarding template assumes."
  deliverables={[
    "HubSpot portal setup or migration — clean data structure, deduplication, and property alignment",
    "Pipeline and deal stage configuration — built to match your lifecycle definitions and handoff rules",
    "Marketing and sales automation — workflows for lead routing, nurturing, task creation, and handoff triggers",
    "Reporting and dashboard setup — custom reports for marketing, sales, and leadership",
    "HubSpot–tool integrations — connections to Salesforce, Slack, LinkedIn, billing tools, or other stack elements",
    "Operations playbook — documentation of how HubSpot is configured, what each workflow does, and how to maintain it",
    "Ongoing operations support option — monthly review, optimization, and maintenance",
  ]}
  faq={[
    {
      q: "Do you work with all HubSpot Hubs?",
      a: "We work primarily with Marketing Hub and Sales Hub. Depending on the engagement, we also support Service Hub configuration for CS workflows and reporting.",
    },
    {
      q: "Can you migrate our data from Salesforce or another CRM?",
      a: "Yes. Data migration — including field mapping, deduplication, and import — is a standard part of HubSpot migration engagements.",
    },
    {
      q: "Is ongoing operations support included?",
      a: "Not automatically. Implementation and ongoing support are scoped separately. Many clients engage us for monthly operations support after initial implementation is complete.",
    },
    {
      q: "How is this different from a HubSpot partner agency?",
      a: "We focus on revenue operations and Japan-facing business logic, not marketing campaigns or content production. Configuration decisions are tied to funnel design and team operating rules — not to what a standard onboarding template assumes.",
    },
  ]}
  japanGTM="HubSpot for Japan-facing operations requires specific configuration decisions: lifecycle stages that reflect Japan's longer trust-building phase, contact properties that capture Japan-relevant qualification data, automation logic that fits Japan's communication and follow-up norms, and reporting that surfaces what matters for Japan's buying cycle. We configure HubSpot to support Japan-facing execution, not just to pass a standard onboarding checklist."
/>
